<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="ITA50">
<l>aḻaippaṉ ṟirumālai yāṅkavarkaḷ coṉṉa</l>
<l>piḻaippil perumpeyarē pēci – yiḻaippariya</l>
<l>vāyavaṉē yātavaṉē yeṉṟavaṉai yārmukappu</l>
<l>māyavaṉē yeṉṟu matittu</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>I invoke Tirumāl, saying the great names</l>
<l>without fault, [as] spoken by those there – envisioning him</l>
<l>who is addressed ‘o cowherd difficult to scrutinize<note xml:lang="en" place="foot">The noun iḻaippu is not included in the TL but can easily be expained as a nomen actionis of iḻaittal, “to determine”.</note>, o Yātavaṉ,’</l>
<l>as Māyavaṉ before all people.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
